OL,3,CThree things we learned from the
OL,4,CRussell Findlay leader interview
OL,6,FFor obvious reasons, independence is
OL,7,Fan especially salient issue across the
OL,8,Fsouth of Scotland.
OL,10,FThat explains at least in part why the
OL,11,Fthree constituencies spanning the
OL,12,Fborder are currently coloured Tory
OL,13,Fblue.
OL,15,FFor context, those are three of the
OL,16,Ffive first past the post seats won by
OL,17,Fthe party in 2021.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/17
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1776341451
OL,3,CThree things we learned from the
OL,4,CRussell Findlay leader interview
OL,6,FMultiple people with knowledge of the
OL,7,FConservative campaign say the south is
OL,8,Fthe only part of the country where
OL,9,Fthey realistically hope to hold up,
OL,10,Fnotwithstanding the challenge from
OL,11,Fboth Reform UK and the SNP.
OL,13,FTo use Mr Findlay's phrasing, this is
OL,14,Fbecause "people put a shift in"
OL,15,Flocally with well-drilled campaigning.
OL,17,FBut he is insistent that unlike other
OL,18,Fparties who are putting a laser-like
OL,19,Ffocus on specific areas to try and
OL,20,Fmaximise a concentrated vote, he is
OL,21,Fnot about to retreat south.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/17
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1776341451
OL,3,CThree things we learned from the
OL,4,CRussell Findlay leader interview
OL,6,F"We are speaking to the whole of
OL,7,FScotland, people across Scotland that
OL,8,Fwant to see some common sense in their
OL,9,Fpolitics and they want to see a
OL,10,FHolyrood parliament focused on the
OL,11,Fissues that matter to them."
OL,13,FSo why isn't that translating into
OL,14,Fsupport for his party? Mr Findlay says
OL,15,Fthere is a "widespread sense of
OL,16,Fdisillusionment from a lot of people
OL,17,Fand I completely get that".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/17
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1776341451
OL,3,CThree things we learned from the
OL,4,CRussell Findlay leader interview
OL,6,FHe is also quick to acknowledge that
OL,7,Fmany voters are not ready to forgive
OL,8,Fthe Conservatives for the performance
OL,9,Fand scandals of last UK government,
OL,10,Fparticularly during the Boris Johnson
OL,11,Fand Liz Truss premierships.
OL,13,FThat disenchantment applies to most
OL,14,Fparties just now but it is currently
OL,15,Fproving to be a particularly hard
OL,16,Fceiling on Mr Findlay's ambitions, no
OL,17,Fmatter how much he tries to raise them.
OL,19,FSafety matters
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/17
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
